Q2) Explain the difference between Checked and Unchecked exceptions. write some
examples of checked and unchecked exception classes.

->
Checked exceptions are exceptions which are must checked or need to handle before compilation. If you dont handle these type
of exceptions then dot class file will not generate.
examples :- ClassNotFoundException, FileNotFoundException.

Unchecked exceptions are exceptions which need not to be handle before compilation it can be ignored and your dot class file
will get gnerate.
examples :- NullPointerException, ArrayOutOfBoundIndexException.